```

As for your provided manifest.json file, it's incompliant with the updated browser extension standards as it's using Manifest version 2. Starting with Firefox 48, Firefox extensions must use Manifest version 3, which requires a different format. Update your manifest.json file to Manifest v3 like this:

manifest.json:
```json
{
  "manifest_version": 3,
  "name": "Auto Clear Data",
  "version": "1.0",
  "description": "Automatically clears cache, cookies, localStorage, indexedDB, and service worker registrations after a specified time interval.",
  "permissions": ["<all_urls>", "storage", "browsingData", "cookies", "notifications"],
  "action": {
    "default_popup": "popup.html",
    "default_icon": {
      "48": "icon48.png" // Add an icon file with this name and size in the same directory
    }
  },
  "background": {
    "service_worker": "background.js"
  }
}
```

Regarding the HTML files, modern Firefox versions still support HTML as the primary markup language for web pages and browser extensions. Place the HTML and JavaScript files inside your extension/addon folder. Make sure to have a popup.html file that includes the user interface code provided above, as well as the additional "script.js" file containing the `clearData()` function.

Here's an overview of the addon's directory structure:

```
/your-addon
  |___ manifest.json
  |___ popup.html
  |___ script.js
  |___ background.js
  |___ icon48.png
```

